  <!-- Focus -->
  <div class="row boxes-project first">
    <div class="col-md-6 text">
      <h2 class='h7'>ABOUT</h2>
      <p>Yearbook Machine is a web based CMS and Social Network that helps collect, curate, and consolidate memories into beautiful physical products. The platform is aimed exclusively at schools, colleges, and universities.</p>
      <p>Enabling users to share memories, stories and photos and then take that information and tailor it. Creating beautiful customised yearbooks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 text">
      <h2 class='h7'>MY ROLE</h2>
      <p>Working closely with both the development team and customer relations. We worked from the ground up to add new life and clarity to the platform.</p>
      <p>We were limited on a technical side to using the existing model, working exclusively with desktop. I focused on revising the layout and visual language throughout. Re-defining the brand from the colour palette, to typography and iconography. Everything was designed to add a high level of simplicity and aesthetic appeal. We aimed not only solving interaction issues, but correctly communicating the power and purpose of the system.</p>
   </div>
